<!DOCTYPE html>
<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"/><meta content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" name="viewport"/><title>USAA Interview Thesis Brief - Russell Dudek</title><link href="styles.css" rel="stylesheet"/></head><body class="doc-body"><div class="doc-toolbar no-print"><a class="primary" href="docs/Russell-Dudek-USAA-Interview-Thesis-Brief.pdf">Download PDF</a><button onclick="window.print()">Print</button><a href="index.html">Candidate Vision</a></div><main class="document"><section class="paper"><div class="doc-header"><div><div class="doc-name">Russell Dudek</div><div class="doc-role">Process Excellence, Automation &amp; Operating Transformation Leader</div></div><div class="doc-contact"><img alt="USAA" class="doc-logo" src="assets/brand/usaa-logo-official.png"/><strong>Russell Dudek</strong><br/>Pittsburgh, PA · Planning relocation to Tampa/St. Petersburg<br/><a href="tel:+14122878640">412.287.8640</a> · <a href="mailto:russelldudek@gmail.com">russelldudek@gmail.com</a><br/><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/russelldudek">linkedin.com/in/russelldudek</a><br/><a href="https://russelldudek.github.io/USAA/">russelldudek.github.io/USAA/</a></div></div><h1 class="brief-title">Interview Thesis Brief</h1><div class="doc-callout"><h2>Candidate thesis</h2><p><strong>Scale the workflow and its assurance together.</strong> Automation should improve member value, employee flow, control evidence, and operating ownership as one system.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><h2>Real mandate</h2><p>Build and lead a process-automation portfolio and team that can identify the right work, select fit-for-purpose platforms, use process intelligence, embed risk and compliance, prove value against KPIs, and convert successful automations into a durable enterprise capability.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><h2>Why now</h2><ul><li>USAA's 2025 public reporting emphasizes member value, simpler digital experiences, improved claims processing, reduced paperwork, and more seamless integration across products and services.</li><li>The role itself explicitly places risk identification, measurement, monitoring, and control inside the Process Excellence mandate.</li><li>Public regulatory context raises the cost of automation that cannot explain ownership, evidence, monitoring, and exception handling.</li></ul></div><div class="doc-section"><h2>Operating tensions</h2><div class="mini-grid"><div class="mini-box"><h3>Speed / assurance</h3><p>Reduce friction without allowing automation velocity to outrun control evidence.</p></div><div class="mini-box"><h3>Standard / variation</h3><p>Create enterprise discipline without flattening legitimate business differences.</p></div><div class="mini-box"><h3>Platform / process</h3><p>Select tools from business and process needs, not vendor gravity.</p></div><div class="mini-box"><h3>ROI / member value</h3><p>Connect economics to visible operating outcomes.</p></div><div class="mini-box"><h3>COE / ownership</h3><p>Centralize capability while keeping outcomes with process owners.</p></div><div class="mini-box"><h3>Automation / judgment</h3><p>Retain human authority where context materially affects the decision.</p></div></div></div><div class="doc-footer"><span>Independent candidate work product for USAA · github.com/russelldudek/USAA</span><span class="page-number">Interview Brief · 1</span></div></section><section class="paper brief-model-page"><div class="doc-header"><div><div class="doc-name">Russell Dudek</div><div class="doc-role">Process Excellence, Automation &amp; Operating Transformation Leader</div></div><div class="doc-contact"><img alt="USAA" class="doc-logo" src="assets/brand/usaa-logo-official.png"/><strong>Russell Dudek</strong><br/>Pittsburgh, PA · Planning relocation to Tampa/St. Petersburg<br/><a href="tel:+14122878640">412.287.8640</a> · <a href="mailto:russelldudek@gmail.com">russelldudek@gmail.com</a><br/><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/russelldudek">linkedin.com/in/russelldudek</a><br/><a href="https://russelldudek.github.io/USAA/">russelldudek.github.io/USAA/</a></div></div><h1 class="brief-title">The Automation Assurance Twin</h1><div class="doc-section"><h2>Two synchronized views</h2><div class="doc-columns"><div><h3>Work plane</h3><ul><li>Member or employee need</li><li>Process steps and handoffs</li><li>Decision logic and exceptions</li><li>Outcome and service effect</li></ul></div><div><h3>Assurance plane</h3><ul><li>Named process and control owner</li><li>Human and machine authority</li><li>Evidence, logs, and traceability</li><li>Monitoring, fallback, and review</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="doc-section"><h2>Portfolio decisions</h2><table class="decision-table"><tr><th>Mode</th><th>Decision logic</th><th>Evidence before scale</th></tr><tr><td><strong>Redesign</strong></td><td>Exceptions and handoffs dominate.</td><td>Root causes, simplified flow, decision rights.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Assist</strong></td><td>Judgment or member context matters.</td><td>Human authority, quality review, override learning.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Automate</strong></td><td>Rules, inputs, exceptions, fallback are stable.</td><td>Control mapping, traceability, monitoring, recovery.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Standardize</strong></td><td>Evidence supports reuse across comparable work.</td><td>Realized value, ownership, reuse boundary, maintenance economics.</td></tr></table></div><div class="doc-section"><h2>Value scorecard</h2><ul><li><strong>Member value:</strong> friction, cycle time, repeat contact, service outcome.</li><li><strong>Employee flow:</strong> touches, rework, queue age, exception burden, retained adoption.</li><li><strong>Control quality:</strong> coverage, traceability, exception closure, monitoring.</li><li><strong>Economics:</strong> labor hours avoided, quality cost, platform and maintenance burden.</li><li><strong>Learning/reuse:</strong> repeated failure modes, change latency, reuse effort, retirement decisions.</li></u